Kang’ata only fell short of asking politicians to draft bills in Parliament to address coffee, tea, avocado, bananas, milk and horticultural products.Murang’a people have previously supported political initiatives but never fully benefited from them. The open letter by Murang’a Senator Irungu Kang’ata has catapulted him into a hero for daring the route Kenneth Matiba took in 1990. However, our era is interesting in that political priorities do not rhyme with economic realities.
Murang’a residents feel deprived and neglected by the current crop of politicians who only seek selfish interests and election survival. Nobody is bothered about these facts since most politicians are so intoxicated in the BBI wine.



